# Learning Progression Path
# Diagramme montrant la progression d'apprentissage recommandee

direction: right

title: {
  label: Learning Progression - From Beginner to Expert
  near: top-center
  shape: text
  style: {
    font-size: 24
    bold: true
  }
}

# Level 1: PowerShell + cURL
level1: "Level 1: Raw HTTP" {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#ffebee"
    stroke: "#c62828"
    font-size: 16
  }
}

level1_details: |md
**01-powershell-curl/**

**You will learn:**
- JSON-RPC structure
- HTTP mechanics (POST, headers)
- Authentication flow
- Raw API responses
- Error handling basics

**Tools:** PowerShell, cURL
**Difficulty:** Beginner
**Time:** 2-4 hours
|

# Level 2: Python + requests
level2: "Level 2: Abstraction" {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#fff3e0"
    stroke: "#f57c00"
    font-size: 16
  }
}

level2_details: |md
**02-python-requests/**

**You will learn:**
- Code organization
- Class-based design
- Error handling (exceptions)
- Type hints
- Reusable modules

**Tools:** Python 3.8+, requests
**Difficulty:** Intermediate
**Time:** 3-5 hours
|

# Level 3: pyFMG
level3: "Level 3: Official SDK" {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#e8f5e9"
    stroke: "#388e3c"
    font-size: 16
  }
}

level3_details: |md
**03-python-pyfmg/**

**You will learn:**
- Official library usage
- Simplified API calls
- Context managers
- API Key authentication
- Production patterns

**Tools:** Python 3.8+, pyFMG
**Difficulty:** Intermediate
**Time:** 2-3 hours
|

# Level 4: Ansible
level4: "Level 4: Infrastructure as Code" {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#e3f2fd"
    stroke: "#1976d2"
    font-size: 16
  }
}

level4_details: |md
**04-ansible/**

**You will learn:**
- Declarative configuration
- Idempotent operations
- Inventory management
- Variable templating
- CI/CD integration

**Tools:** Ansible Core 2.15+
**Difficulty:** Advanced
**Time:** 4-6 hours
|

# Connections
level1 -> level2: "Master HTTP basics"
level2 -> level3: "Learn abstraction"
level3 -> level4: "Production ready"

level1 -> level1_details
level2 -> level2_details
level3 -> level3_details
level4 -> level4_details

# Prerequisites
prereqs: Prerequisites {
  shape: callout
  style: {
    fill: "#f3e5f5"
    stroke: "#7b1fa2"
  }
}

prereqs_text: |md
**Before starting:**
1. FortiManager access (7.2.x - 7.6.x)
2. Admin credentials or API Key
3. Basic networking knowledge
4. Command line familiarity
|

# Goal
goal: Expert Level {
  shape: oval
  style: {
    fill: "#c8e6c9"
    stroke: "#388e3c"
    font-size: 18
    bold: true
  }
}

goal_text: |md
**You can now:**
- Automate FortiManager operations
- Build custom tools
- Integrate with CI/CD
- Manage at scale
|

prereqs -> prereqs_text
prereqs -> level1
level4 -> goal
goal -> goal_text

